//! Scheduler contract state reading for scheduled transaction verification
//!
//! Reads Scheduler contract storage for validity constraint checks (C1-C11).
//! Uses similar storage reading patterns as ritual-async-registry crate.
//!
//! # Constraints Verified
//!
//! | ID | Constraint | Description |
//! |----|------------|-------------|
//! | C1 | Existence | callId exists in Scheduler |
//! | C2 | State | call.state == SCHEDULED |
//! | C3 | Index Bounds | executionIndex < numCalls |
//! | C4 | Min Block | block.number >= expectedBlock |
//! | C5 | Max Block (TTL) | block.number <= expectedBlock + TTL |
//! | C6 | Expiry | block.number <= overallExpiryBlock |
//! | C7 | Sender | msg.sender == SYSTEM_ACCOUNT |
//! | C8 | Target | tx.to == SCHEDULER |
//! | C9 | Funds | caller has sufficient funds in RitualWallet |
//! | C10 | Uniqueness | (callId, index) not executed before |
//! | C11 | Predicate | User-defined predicate returns true |

